Robt Mann wrote:
>
>  fingers, feel the plug into the hole, turn it gently anticlockwise to 
> feel the thread-start, and then gently turn the tube-spanner clockwise 
> to thread the plug 
I think the above is really important.  I *always* spin screws backwards 
until I feel the threads seat correctly and then I start spinning them 
forward.  This almost always helps to avoid cross-threading.

Mike
